 :: _sequence_, aesop's fables, aesop, two good friends and the bear, the story ::

Yí wèi =shāngrén hé yí wèi =nóngfū =jiébàn =tóngxíng, tāmen yào =jīngguò ="yí gè méiyǒurén yān de shùlín".
   " (ph) 一位商人和一位农夫结伴同行，他们要经过一个没有人烟的树林。
   " (pe) A merchant and a farmer were travelling together. They needed to pass through a forest with no trace/whiff/mist of people. 
   " (llm) A merchant and a farmer travelled together. They needed to pass through an uninhabited forest.



="Nàlǐ shì wēixiǎn dìdài", suǒyǐ tāmen =yuēhǎo le, =wúlùn =yùjiàn shénme =wēixiǎn, liǎng gè rén dōu yào xiānghù =bāngzhù. 
   " (ph) 那里是危险地带，所以他们约好了，无论遇见什么危险，两个人都要相互帮助。
   " (pe) It was a dangerous place so they made a pact that no matter what danger they experienced they would help each other.
   " (llm) It was a dangerous area, so they made an agreement that no matter what danger they encountered, both of them would help each other.



Tāmen zǒujìn shùlín bù jiǔ, =wēixiǎn =jiùlái lín le —— yì zhī dà xióng =cóng qiánmiàn =cháo tā men zǒu lái.
   " (ph) 他们走进树林不久，危险就来临了——一只大熊从前面朝他们走来。
   " (pe) They hadn't gone far through the forest when danger suddenly was upon them. A large bear was walking towards them from up ahead.
   " (llm) Not long after they walked into the forest, danger arrived—a big bear was walking toward them from up ahead.

# jiù  soon / suddenly
# láilín 来临  arrived

Shāngrén dòngzuò mǐnjié, tā gǎnkuài páshàng zuìjìn de dà shù duǒ qǐlái. 
   " (ph) 商人动作敏捷，他赶快爬上最近的大树躲起来。
   " (pe) The merchant acted with agility, quickly climbing the nearest large tree to hide.
   " (llm) The merchant moved quickly and nimbly; he immediately climbed up the nearest large tree to hide.

# páshàng 爬上 climbup
# zuìjìn 最近 recent/nearest
# qǐlái 起来 upwards
# dòngzuò 动作 action
# mǐnjié 敏捷 agile nimble
# duǒ  躲 hide
# gǎnkuài 赶快 quickly/hurriedly

=kě nóngfū =bàozhe shù =gànjiù shì pá bú =shàngqù, tā =zhǐhǎo =gǎnkuài tǎng zài =dìshang =zhuāngsǐ.
   " (ph) 可农夫抱着树干就是爬不上去，他只好赶快躺在地上装死。
   " (pe) But the farmer hugging the tree just couldn't climb up, he was forced to quickly lie on the ground and play dead.
   " (llm) But the farmer hugged the tree trunk and just couldn't climb up, so he had no choice but to quickly lie on the ground and pretend to be dead.
   " (note) This sentence starts with 可/kě is used here as a shortened, spoken form of 但是/dànshì or 可是/kěshì, meaning "but" or "however". Gemini informs: what makes this sentence work so well is the relationship between 可/kě at the beginning and 就是/jiùshì in the middle: 可 flags to the listener: "Pay attention, a problem is coming!" 说明/就是 emphasizes the total frustration or helplessness of the situation: "He tried, but he just couldn't do it." If you were reading this fable out loud, that initial 可 is the exact moment the tension spikes for the character!

# bàozhe 抱着 hug / embrace / carry in arms
# jiùshì 就是 exactly
# pá 爬 climb
# shàngqù 上去 go up
# dìshang 地上 ground
# tǎng 躺 lie
# zhǐhǎo 只好 forced to
# zhuāngsǐ 装死 play dead
# gànjiù 干就 just do it
# kě 可 but short for 可是 meaning but

xióng =zǒujìn hòu, kànjiàn tǎng zài dìshang de nóngfū, jiù guòlái yòng bízi wén, bìngwéi ràozhe tā rào le bàntiān.
   "  (ph) 熊走近后，看见躺在地上的农夫，就过来用鼻子闻，并围绕着他绕了半天。
   "  (pe) After the bear got close, it saw the farmer lying on the ground and came over to sniff using its nose, circling around him for a long time.
   "  (llm) After the bear approached, it saw the farmer lying on the ground. It came over to sniff him with its nose and circled around him for a long time. 

# zǒujìn 走近 approach / get closer
# jiù 就 immediately 
# guòlái 过来 come over
# bízi 鼻子 nose
# wén 闻 smell
# bìngwéi 并围 encircle
# ràozhe 绕着 circle around
# bàntiān 半天 long time



nóngfū jǐnbì shuāng yǎn, bǐngzhù hūxī, yí dòng yě bú dòng.
   "  (ph) 农夫紧闭双眼，屏住呼吸，一动也不动。
   "  (pe) The farmer closed his eyes tightly, held his breath, and kept perfectly still. 
   "  (llm) The farmer shut his eyes tightly, held his breath, and did not move at all.

# jǐnbì 紧闭 tightly closed
# bǐngzhù / pǐngzhù 屏住 hold, e.g. breath
