# caption
shāngrén kàndào xióng xiàng tāmen zǒu lái, biàn rēngxià nóngfū, yí gè rén pá dào shù shàng duǒ cáng qǐ lái.
   " (ph) 商人看到熊向他们走来，便扔下农夫，一个人爬到树上躲藏起来。
   " (pe) Seeing the bear walking toward them, the merchant abandoned the farmer and climbed the tree alone to hide.

# kàndào 看到 sê
# rēngxià 扔下 abandon/ditch/leave behind
# biàn 便 immediately

 dà xióng yǐwéi nóngfū zhēnde shì gè sǐ rén, jiù zǒukāi le. yīnwèi xióng shì bù chī sǐ rén de.
  " (ph) 大熊以为农夫真的是个死人，就走开了。因为熊是不吃死人的。
  " (pe) The great bear presumed the farmer really was a dead person, and soon walked away, because bears be like don't eat dead people yo!
  " (llm) The bear thought the farmer was truly a dead person, so it walked away. Because bears do not eat dead people.

# yǐwéi 以为 presume / believe mistakenly
# zhēnde 真的 really
# zǒukāi 走开 go away

zhídào dà xióng zǒuyuǎn le, shāngrén cái cóng shù shàng xiàlai, nóngfū yě pá le qǐlái. shāngrén jiù wèn nóngfū: “péngyou, dàxióng gāngcái fúzài nǐ de ěr páng gēn nǐ shuō le xiē shénme ya?”
   " (ph) 直到大熊走远了，商人才从树上下来，农夫也爬了起来。商人就问农夫：“朋友,大熊刚才伏在你的耳旁跟你说了些什么呀？”
   " (pe) Knowing that the bear had gone, the merchant only then came down from up in the tree. the farmer also got up. The merchant then asked the farmer: "Friend, when the great bear was leaning over you just now, what did he whisper in your ear?"
   " (llm) Not until the big bear had walked far away did the merchant come down from the tree, and the farmer climbed up from the ground too. The merchant then asked the farmer, "My friend, what did the big bear whisper right next to your ear just now?"

# cái 才 not until [when before a time expression]
# xiàlai 下来 come down
# cóng shù shàng 从树上 from up in the tree
# fúzài 伏在 means "leaning over," "crouching down close to," or "bending over."
# qǐlái  起来 stand up
# gāngcái 刚才 just now
# nǐ de ěr páng 你的耳旁 beside your ear
# nǐ de ěr páng gēn nǐ shuōle xiē shénme ya 你的耳旁跟你说了些什么呀 What was whispered in your ear?

nóngfū zhuāngzuò háo bú zàihu de yàngzi, bù jǐn bú màn de shuō: “dà xióng dàoshì méi hé wǒ shuō shénme mìmì, tā zhǐshì gàosu wǒ, xiàcì bú yào zài hé méi yǒu xìnyòng de rén jiāo péng you la!”
    " (ph) 农夫装作毫不在乎的样子，不紧不慢地说：“大熊倒是没和我说什么秘密，它只是告诉我，下次不要再和没有信用的人交朋友/ ！”
    " (pe) The farmer, pretending not to care, evenly replied: "Actually, the great bear didn't speak any secrets, he only told me that next time don't make friends with untrustworthy people." 
    " (llm) Pretending not to care at all, the farmer said calmly and unhurriedly, "The big bear didn't actually tell me any secrets. It only told me not to make friends with untrustworthy people next time!"

# zàihu 在乎 to care
# xìnyòng 信用 trustworthiness / credibility / good faith. (contains) xìn 信 trust, believe, or honesty as used in 信用卡 xìnyòngkǎ: Credit card (literally, "trust-use card")

# zhuāngzuò 装作 pretend to

shāngrén tīng le, =xiūkuì dei dīxià le tóu.
   " (ph) 商人听了，羞愧地低下了头。
   " (pe) hearing this, the merchant lowered his head in shame.

# dīxià 低下 low
# xiūkuì dei dīxià 羞愧地低下 lowered in shame
# yàngzi 样子 appearance
# Bù jǐn bù màn de shuō 不紧不慢地说 Speaking in a measured, unhurried manner
# dàoshì 倒是 actually/ ơn the contrary - a bit sarcastic
# mìmì 秘密 secret
# zhǐshì 只是 only
# xiàcì 下次 next time

# méi yǒu xìn yòng de rén 没有信用的人 uncreditworthy untrustworthy person
# jiāo péng you 交朋友 make friends

